{"updated_at": "2011-08-29T18:52:57Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-08-29T18:51:47Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1934950", "id": 1934950, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2734", "issue_id": 2734, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/dmathieu", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "6fa1cdda524d49996a8bc6917328de3d", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/6fa1cdda524d49996a8bc6917328de3d?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F71ee911dd06428a96c143a0b135041a4.png", "id": 9347, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu/events{/privacy}", "login": "dmathieu", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmathieu/followers"}, "body": "I don't think having all the core contributors included is a good idea.\r\nIt gives the impression that core contributors are the only ones working on rails, which is not the case.\r\nMoreover, the list of core contributors can change. When someone loses their core contributor right for any reason, removing them from this list could be perceived as considering their work to be useless, which is not the case.\r\n\r\nWhy not just provide a link to the [contributors page](http://contributors.rubyonrails.org/) ?", "_id": {"$oid": "523fa3adbd354364b9019b63"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2734#issuecomment-1934950"}
